'''''Wizardry''''' (also known as '''''Spell of Destruction''''') is an [[adventure game]] with some action and role-playing elements, published by [[Edge Games|The Edge]] in 1985 for the [[Commodore 64]]. It was programmed by Steven T. Chapman (author of [[Quo Vadis (1984 video game)|Quo Vadis]]) and the music was composed by Clever Music (Graham Jarvis and Rob Hartshorne) under the alias of Mike Alsop.

==Reception==
''[[Zzap!64]]'' were impressed by the game's graphics and sound but found the puzzles overly obscure.  It was rated 71% overall.<ref>[http://www.zzap64.co.uk/cgi-bin/displaypage.pl?issue=007&page=015&magazine=zzap Review: Wizardry], [[Zzap!64]], page 015 from issue 007, November 1985</ref> ''[[Commodore User]]'' 11/1985	gave 4.2 of 5 stars.<ref>[http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/original/7/73970/2897686-commodore_user_11_1985_042.jpg Commodore User 11/1985 page 42], [http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/original/7/73970/2897687-commodore_user_11_1985_043.jpg page 43]</ref> ''[[Computer and Video Games]]'' 12/1985 rated the game 90 of 100.<ref>[http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/original/7/73970/2897688-cvg_12_1985_014.jpg Computer and Video Games 12/1985 page 14], [http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/original/7/73970/2897689-cvg_12_1985_015.jpg page 15]</ref> Eric Doyle of ''[[Your Commodore]]'' praised the game's graphics, music, and "engrossing and enjoyable" puzzle element. He gave it 7 out of 10 for originality, 8 out of 10 for both playability and value for money, and 9 out of 10 for graphics.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Doyle|first=Eric|title=Action Replay: Wizardry|magazine=[[Your Commodore]]|date=January 1986|page=52|url=http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/original/7/73970/2897691-your_commodore_01_1986_052.jpg|accessdate=21 May 2017}}</ref> German computer magazine ''Happy Computer'' 11/1986 gave 74 of 100.<ref>[http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/original/7/73970/2897690-happy_computer_sh11_1986_120.jpg Happy Computer 11/1986 page 120]</ref>

